 understanding of his poetry among those who have followed it for many years and students and other readers encountering this major poet for the first time.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  aGeoffrey Hill.  aScenes from Comus.  alanguage.  apitch.  apoems.  apoetry.  arecalcitrance.  asatiric.  asorrowing.  autterance.1 aWainwright, Jeffrey, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779396640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847793966423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847793966/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles